        impact: 'The learner surface for the curriculum: enrolled users see a topic catalog, drill into concepts through a 5-tab shell (Primer / Lab / Check-in / Notes / Teach), submit lab attempts through a 202-async pattern with fire-and-forget CODE_REVIEW review, poll for verdicts, gate-reveal the reference solution, run PASS/FAIL check-ins, and see all three source signals (primer_read, practice, checkin) accumulate on ConceptMastery. WebSocket `curriculum:review_ready` event notifies the client the instant an attempt review completes. Full learner journey is E2E-tested against Postgres — enroll → primer → attempt (STRONG mock) → poll → reveal → check-in (PASS mock) → verify all three signals persisted, all 12 steps in one continuous test.',
        description: '10 commits over the week. Server: curriculum.controller.js exposes 9 learner routes — GET /topics (catalog), GET /topics/:slug (detail with enrollment + concept tree), POST /topics/:slug/enroll (idempotent, returns 201), GET /concepts/:slug (5-tab payload with mastery + lab shape but never reference), POST /labs/:id/attempts (202 PENDING + fire-and-forget CODE_REVIEW via .then() chain matching teaching.controller precedent), GET /labs/:id/attempts/:id (polling), POST /labs/:id/reveal-reference (gated by prior STRONG attempt — 403 REVEAL_BLOCKED_NO_ATTEMPT otherwise), POST /concepts/:slug/checkin (gated by revealed lab — 403 CHECKIN_LOCKED otherwise), POST /concepts/:slug/mark-primer-read (idempotent 200). server/src/services/curriculum/conceptMastery.service.js delegates to mentor.service.updateMastery with positional args + JSON signal shape {source, value, evidence, at}. mentor.service.js grew a SIGNAL_WEIGHTS.checkin = 0.30 entry. server/src/services/websocket.service.js sendToUser(userId, message) fans out curriculum:review_ready events the instant onReviewCompleted transitions LabAttempt.reviewStatus to COMPLETED. Client: 9 TanStack Query hooks in useCurriculumLearn.js — useLearnCatalog, useTopicDetail, useConceptDetail, useEnrollInTopic, useSubmitAttempt, useAttempt (polling with refetchInterval that stops on COMPLETED), useRevealReference, useSubmitCheckIn, useMarkPrimerRead, plus useCurriculumReviewReady WS subscription. LearnPage.jsx rewrite (topic cards grid). TopicDetailPage.jsx rewrite (enrollment card + concept tree with per-concept mastery preview). ConceptPage.jsx rewrite as 5-tab shell with ?tab= URL param — Primer (rendered HTML + mark-read button), Lab (Monaco stub + submit + polling), Check-in (3-question form + calibrationDelta), Notes (linked notes surface), Teach (placeholder until Phase 2). E2E test walks all 12 journey steps against real Postgres with STRONG + PASS mocks via _overrideValidatorSpec, verifies primer_read + practice + checkin signals + ConceptMastery.score > 0 + teachingReady=false (Phase-2 wiring will flip that assertion). Fixed pre-existing parallel-run prefix-collision flake: curriculumAdmin.topic.integration.test.js used TEST_PREFIX="test_curradm_" which was a substring of "test_curradm_c_" (concept) and "test_curradm_l_" (lab) — renamed to "test_curradm_t_" for symmetry, cleaned up 9 FK-violation failures under parallel test-file execution.',
        why: 'Weeks 1-3 shipped the authoring side (feature flag, WS user-targeting, sanitize primitives, team-scoped Prisma models, sync pipeline, AI validators, admin authoring UI + fork flow). Week 4 is the moment where an enrolled learner can actually consume the content: browse topics, work a lab, get AI review, reveal reference, take a check-in, watch mastery accrue. Without this UI, the Week 1-3 machinery is unreachable to end users. The 202-async attempt pattern (POST returns PENDING immediately, review runs in the background, client polls or listens on WS) matches the teaching.controller precedent and keeps the request path fast — a slow CODE_REVIEW call cannot block the API for other users. The three-tier gate architecture (mark-read = free, attempt = anytime, reveal = gated by STRONG attempt, check-in = gated by reveal) enforces the pedagogical loop from the LLD template: learners must struggle before they see the answer, and reflect after they solve.',
        researchBasis: 'Fire-and-forget async pattern with state-machine reviewStatus (PENDING → REVIEWING → COMPLETED/ERROR) follows the standard command-query separation pattern and matches the existing teaching.controller LiveRoom precedent — one canonical async shape in the codebase. Reveal-gate on prior STRONG attempt follows the retrieval-practice literature (Karpicke & Roediger 2008 — testing before seeing the answer produces durable learning; premature reveal collapses to re-reading which produces near-zero long-term retention). Check-in-gate on revealed lab follows Kluger & DeNisi 1996 feedback intervention theory (feedback works only when the learner has an existing mental model to update — check-in AFTER lab + reference produces the productive-failure sequence, not the opposite). ConceptMastery signal weighting (primer_read=0.0, practice=0.5, checkin=0.3, teaching=0.2) follows Bloom (1968) mastery learning + Fiorella-Mayer (2013) learning-by-teaching — different sources produce different depth of learning; primer_read is bookkeeping (learner has been exposed), practice is verified application, checkin is retrieval-strength, teaching is elaborative encoding. 202-with-polling for AI review completion matches synthetic-monitoring industry practice (Datadog, PagerDuty Synthetics) — long-running work MUST NOT block the API request path.',
        technicalNotes: 'server/src/controllers/curriculum.controller.js + routes/curriculum.routes.js (9 learner routes at /api/v1/curriculum/*, mounted inside mountRoutes with apiLimiter). server/src/services/curriculum/conceptMastery.service.js (recordLabSignal / recordCheckInSignal / recordPrimerReadSignal — thin delegators to mentor.service.updateMastery with positional args + JSON signal shape). server/src/services/mentor.service.js — added SIGNAL_WEIGHTS.checkin = 0.30. server/src/services/websocket.service.js sendToUser(userId, message) fans out to all sockets matching ws.userId. Fire-and-forget CODE_REVIEW via .then() chain (onReviewCompleted transitions reviewStatus + writes practice signal + emits WS event). client/src/services/curriculumLearn.api.js + hooks/useCurriculumLearn.js (9 hooks + WS subscription). client/src/pages/learn/{LearnPage,TopicDetailPage,ConceptPage}.jsx rewrites. client/src/pages/learn/tabs/{ConceptPrimerTab,ConceptLabTab,ConceptCheckInTab,ConceptNotesTab,ConceptTeachTab}.jsx (5-tab shell with ?tab= URL param). server/test/integration/curriculum.learnerJourney.e2e.integration.test.js (608 lines — 12-step E2E from enroll through all three signals). Fixed pre-existing parallel-run prefix collision (curriculumAdmin.topic test prefix renamed test_curradm_ → test_curradm_t_ for symmetry with _c_ and _l_ tests). 25 files changed (+7,724 / -733); server tests: 1819/1819 passing (baseline was 1765 at Week 3 close — Week 4 added 54 tests). Pre-push gate green across all 7 checks. Deferred to Week 5+: LabPage Monaco editor upgrade, D8 mapping + signal-to-verdict wiring, teachingReady truth-table flip (writer that flips on PASS check-in + STRONG lab), signal-source diversification (currently 3 sources; Phase 2 adds teaching + retrieval).',
