        title: 'Curriculum Phase 1 · Week 3 (TEAM_ADMIN authoring UI + fork flow)',
        impact: 'The authoring surface for the curriculum: TEAM_ADMIN users can fork a repo-authored TopicTemplate into a team-scoped Topic in one atomic transaction, then edit primer / concepts / labs through a 4-tab UI that routes every write through team-scoped Prisma queries, XML-fenced sanitization, and (for Topic + Concept) the Week 2 validate-or-fallback AI review pipeline. Publish gates enforce quality at the boundary — Topic requires WORTH_LEARNING verdict + every concept PUBLISHED, Concept requires READY verdict + rubric present, Lab is deterministic shape-check (no AI). SUPER_ADMIN cross-team writes are audit-logged to CurriculumAdminAuditLog. The full fork → edit → review → publish flow is E2E-tested against a real Postgres.',
        description: '13 commits over the week. Server: curriculumFork.service.js deep-clones TopicTemplate → Topic + all ConceptTemplates → Concepts + all LabTemplates → Labs in a single interactive Prisma transaction with 409 on duplicate slug (unique index (teamId, slug) trap avoided). curriculumAdmin.controller.js exposes Topic CRUD (POST /from-template, GET list, GET detail, PATCH, DELETE), Concept CRUD (POST, PATCH, DELETE with 1:1 Lab preserved), Lab CRUD, review-trigger routes (POST /topics/:id/review, POST /concepts/:id/review — call Week 2 contentReview.service.js orchestrator), and publish-gate routes (POST /topics/:id/publish, POST /concepts/:id/publish, POST /labs/:id/publish — enforce dual gates deterministically before flipping status). Every write is TEAM_ADMIN-gated + req.teamId-scoped. SUPER_ADMIN team-override writes log to CurriculumAdminAuditLog with (userId, teamId, action, resourceType, resourceId, diff) — read via GET /platform/curriculum/audit-log. Client: three shared UI primitives — VerdictBadge (WORTH_LEARNING / WITH_ADJUSTMENTS / NOT_WORTH_TIME / READY / POLISH / NOT_READY color-coded), PublishGateChecklist (per-gate PASS/FAIL with the failure reason inlined), MarkdownEditor (lazy-loaded @uiw/react-md-editor, theme-aware, XSS-safe preview via existing DOMPurify config). CurriculumAdminPage (status board grouped by DRAFT / IN_REVIEW / PUBLISHED / ARCHIVED with per-Topic verdict badge + gate checklist). TemplateBrowserPage (grid of TopicTemplates with fork button — POST /from-template with optimistic UI + 409-duplicate handling). TopicAuthoringPage (4 tabs: metadata / concepts / review / publish — each tab bounded, keyboard-navigable, saves via TanStack Query mutation with useToastingMutation). Full E2E integration test drives fork → edit primer → edit concept → trigger review → publish through wire-level POST/PATCH calls against Postgres. Fixed a pre-existing curriculumSync test flake (fixture slugs collided under vitest parallel test-file execution — prefixed with test_sync_).',
