        title: 'Curriculum Phase 1 — flip FEATURE_CURRICULUM=true in production',
        impact: 'The staging flip fires at end of W6. Production flip follows after one week of green metrics. Turns the whole curriculum feature (author + learner surfaces + auto-flipping teachingReady + D8 adapter) from OFF to ON for every existing team. Learners can enroll in published topics, submit lab attempts, take check-ins, and see their teachingReady flip in the mastery panel. Authors can fork templates and publish content for their team.',
        description: 'Post-staging-flip week-long observation, then production flip. Steps: (1) Verify Railway log retention is set intentionally (not default 7-day) for the four telemetry events (`signal_shift_delta`, `reveal_reference_verdict`, `teachingReady_flipped`, `checkin_gate_blocked`). Behavioral analytics data needs ≥30 days for weekly-cohort analysis. (2) Query staging Railway logs for one week — expected: at least one signal_shift_delta per active learner; teachingReady_flipped rate roughly matches the count of learners who complete both a STRONG lab + PASS check-in; reveal_reference_verdict should NOT be firing before any STRONG/ADEQUATE attempt exists (validates the gate). If checkin_gate_blocked events fire heavily with no matching signal_shift_delta for source=checkin, the check-in tab is being reached but not cleared — investigate before prod flip. (3) Run the manual golden-path walkthrough on staging (fork template → publish → enroll → submit → reveal → check-in → verify teachingReady). (4) After 7 days of clean staging data, flip prod: Railway prod service → `FEATURE_CURRICULUM=true` + `VITE_FEATURE_CURRICULUM=true` + `FEATURE_TEACHING_SESSIONS=true` + `FEATURE_NOTES_ENABLED=true`; trigger a REDEPLOY (not restart — VITE flag is baked at build time). (5) Verify prod flag via `curl` on the topics endpoint + grep the deployed client bundle. (6) Announce feature availability internally.',
        why: 'Feature is code-complete after W6; the remaining risk is not "does the code work" but "does the code work at real user traffic." One-week staging soak lets us observe: signal-write patterns match expected distributions, no crash-loops from a missed edge case, telemetry emits at the shape post-ship queries assume. Prod flip is a Railway env change + redeploy, not a code change — so this NEXT entry is process, not engineering. Delaying prod flip until staging metrics are green is the standard SRE canary pattern applied to feature flags.',
        technicalNotes: 'Railway staging service already has curriculum routes reachable — the W6 T8 server-side FEATURE_CURRICULUM guard closes the AI-quota abuse vector before flip. Staging → prod delta: set 4 env vars (2 server, 2 client), trigger redeploy on both services. Verification: `curl -sH "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" https://<prod-server>/api/v1/curriculum/topics | jq` — expect 200 with `{ data: { topics: [] } }` (or non-empty if any team has published). `curl -s https://<prod-client>/assets/index-<hash>.js | grep -o "VITE_FEATURE_CURRICULUM[^;]*"` — expect the `true` value baked in. Rollback plan: flip all four env vars back to false + redeploy. Zero schema changes = zero rollback risk. Monitoring: the four telemetry events feed Railway log queries; if any of them start emitting anomalies (e.g., teachingReady_flipped rate spikes suspiciously, or a spike of signal_shift_delta with `delta < 0` which shouldn\'t happen because signals only add), pause the rollout. Track outstanding follow-ups: `primer_markdown` adversarial injection test (defense exists, test missing); vitest parallel-file flake investigation (2-3 known-flaky tests under high load — not new to W6 but should be scoped before Phase 2 kicks off).',
