        description: 'Prisma migration: `Lab.starterCode: String → starterFiles: Json` shaped `{ "Main.java": "…", "Vehicle.java": "…" }`. Same for `Lab.referenceSolution → referenceFiles: Json` and `LabAttempt.code → files: Json`. Backfill migration converts existing single-file rows to a `{ "Solution.<ext>": <existing string> }` shape so no existing lab breaks. CODE_REVIEW prompt template updated to accept + reason over a file-map (XML-fence each file, name + language + body). Monaco editor gains a top-of-editor tab bar + new-file / rename-file / delete-file affordances (with a per-lab file cap, e.g., 8). Draft persistence extends to the file-map (localStorage key still `curriculum:lab:draft:${labId}` but value is JSON). New integration test `curriculum.autosave-collision.integration.test.js` covers the multi-file + multi-tab collision policy. Also revisits the AI review dimension scoring — with multi-file the reviewer can score `designQuality` against actual module structure instead of inferring it from a single blob.',
