        description: 'Outbox pattern: every embedding-needing write inserts a row in EmbeddingOutbox(entityType, entityId, status, attempts, lastError, nextAttemptAt). Background worker picks up rows with status=PENDING + nextAttemptAt<=now() and attempts the OpenAI call with exponential backoff. Success → write embedding column + delete outbox row. Failure → increment attempts + push nextAttemptAt + record lastError. Diagnostics dashboard surfaces backlog size.',
        why: 'Silent NULL embeddings degrade Recommended Next + Notes Related + similarity-based features without any signal that something\'s broken. Reliability hit per OpenAI bad day.',
        technicalNotes: 'New EmbeddingOutbox model. Background worker (60s setInterval, CAS row claiming). Solution / Note / Problem create paths enqueue instead of calling embedding.service directly. Diagnostics page shows backlog.',
